-- Peru Tax Collection Rose 13 Percent in 2011, Agency Says
-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 2012-02-01T22:34:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-01/peru-tax-collection-rose-13-percent-in-2011-agency-says.html
Peru’s  tax collection  rose 13 percent
to 75.5 billion soles ($28.1 billion) last year compared with
2010, the government said.  Tax collection was equivalent to 16 percent of the
country’s gross domestic product, the highest since 2008, said
the state tax and import duty collection agency known as  Sunat 
in an e-mailed statement.  Tax collection rose 10 percent last month from a year
earlier, the agency said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
